```json
{
  "application": "COBALT",
  "details": {
    "queue": "default",
    "account": "PSFMat",
    "nodes": 128,
    "time": "60",
    "output": "validation",
    "email": "xw111luoye@gmail.com",
    "system": "cetus.alcf.anl.gov",
    "compiler": "Clang++11",
    "git_repository": "https://github.com/QMCPACK/qmcpack.git",
    "build_types": [
      "build_BGQ_${compiler}_real_SoA",
      "build_BGQ_${compiler}_complex_SoA",
      "build_BGQ_${compiler}_real",
      "build_BGQ_${compiler}_complex",
      "build_BGQ_${compiler}_MP_real",
      "build_BGQ_${compiler}_MP_complex"
    ],
    "test_suites": [
      "short",
      "unit",
      "qe-LiH-unpolarized-no-collect-np-16-12-12-nk-16-2-2"
    ],
    "test_executables": [
      "dmc",
      "opt",
      "csvmc",
      "short-H4-opt"
    ],
    "cmake_toolchain_file": "../config/BGQ_${compiler}_ToolChain.cmake",
    "ctest_script": "../CMake/ctest_script.cmake"
  }
}
```

This script is running on the COBALT workload manager. 

**Details about the software and resource requirements:**

* **COBALT:** A workload manager used for scheduling and managing jobs on the cetus.alcf.anl.gov system. 
* **Queue:** "default" - The job is submitted to the default queue.
* **Account:** "PSFMat" - The job is charged to this account.
* **Nodes:** 128 - The job requires 128 compute nodes.
* **Time:** "60" - The job has a time limit of 60 minutes.
* **Output:** "validation" - The output of the job is directed to the "validation" directory.
* **Email:** "xw111luoye@gmail.com" - The user will receive email notifications about the job.
* **System:** "cetus.alcf.anl.gov" - The job is run on this specific computing system.
* **Compiler:** "Clang++11" - The C++ compiler used for building the project.
* **Git repository:** "https://github.com/QMCPACK/qmcpack.git" - The script clones this repository to build the QMCPACK software.
* **Build Types:** The script defines multiple build configurations for different versions and precision levels of the QMCPACK software.
* **Test Suites:** The script specifies various test suites for executing the built QMCPACK binaries.
* **Test Executables:** The script defines specific executables to be tested.
* **CMake Toolchain File:** This file provides instructions for building the QMCPACK project on the BGQ system.
* **CTest Script:** This script is used for executing tests and collecting results.
